[
  "Low-profile founder of Nirma, Karsanbhai Patel, started out mixing detergents in his backyard and selling them door-to-door on his bicycle.",
  "His low-price Nirma brand sparked a detergents war with bigger rivals such as Unilever and Procter & Gamble.",
  "Today Nirma is one of the largest producers of soda ash in the world.",
  "Patel has long handed over operations to the next generation and took the company private in 2012.",
  "His cement unit, Nuvoco Vistas, completed the $730 million acquisition of Emami Cement in July 2020. "
]